{"v":1,"id":"Jvstl7JIFuPHXsTBsvuF","createdAt":"2026-07-08T21:44:10.398Z","app":{"name":"AxiVale","version":"1.3.2"},"kind":"conversation","title":"hey can you run a commander report on this monday's raid?","turns":[{"userText":"hey can you run a commander report on this monday's raid?","agentText":"\n\nMonday's raid under **Not Haro** was a strong night — 32-13 in fights (71% win rate) and a squad K/D of 1.63, with the squad landing 868 enemy downs against 575 of its own.\n\nQuick caveat before the numbers: this Monday (July 6) has exactly **one** published run — `20260706-181017-zgku`, \"Not Haro\", 32 in squad. \"Not Haro\" is a tag alias that doesn't appear in the cross-run commander rollup, so there's no multi-night history to trend against — this is a single-raid review. Combat replay wasn't captured for this run either (positioning returned `degree: none`), so I can't add spatial/out-of-position analysis; enable precise replay in AxiBridge if you want that next time.\n\nHere's how the top damage/kill-pressure carried under the tag — down-contribution across the squad's heaviest hitters:\n\n{{figure}}\n\nTop squad performers under the tag that night — the frontline carries plus the strip and cleanse anchors:\n\n| Player | Prof | Damage | Down contrib | Strips | Cleanses / Heal | Deaths |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| undiee.3146 | Berserker | 16.4M | 3.44M | 15 | — | 10 |\n| Brotalist.3085 | Berserker | 15.1M | 3.44M | 24 | — | 10 |\n| Izathel.4058 | Tempest | 15.6M | 2.53M | 15 | — | 6 |\n| General Moo.7930 | Reaper | 10.9M | 2.14M | 2,661 | — | 10 |\n| Zietlogik.6208 | Reaper | 7.82M | 1.51M | 3,185 | — | 10 |\n| Arx.9785 | Druid | 0.52M | 73K | 22 | 5,807 clr / 9.83M heal | 6 |\n| RedBeard.5743 | Specter | 0.70M | 131K | 41 | 4,668 clr / 5.75M heal | 8 |\n| FatherHyperion.1047 | Troubadour | 0.77M | 124K | 29 | 2,112 clr / 5.23M heal | 5 |\n\nFull 38-player breakdown is in the Actions panel.\n\n**Strengths**\n- **Won the fights convincingly** — 32-13 (71%) over 45 fights, with enemy downs (868) and deaths (481) both well ahead of the squad's own (575 downs / 296 deaths), a 1.63 K/D. The tag was picking winnable fights and closing them.\n- **Excellent boon-strip coverage against a bigger enemy** (avg 37 vs your 32) — four Reapers plus a Necro stacked 12,000+ strips (General Moo 2,661; Zietlogik 3,185; VincentCross 2,316; Anhuur 2,242), which is what let the frontline convert 868 downs.\n- **Sustain held up** — Druids and Specters (Arx 9.8M heal/5,807 cleanses, RedBeard, Oceanomega, Eliare) kept squad deaths to 296 across 45 fights despite being outnumbered most engagements.\n\n**Coaching points**\n- **Squad deaths are high in absolute terms** — 296 deaths / 575 downs means ~51% of your downs became deaths. Against a squad you're out-downing 868-to-575, more of those downs should be getting rallied; look at whether pushes are over-extending past cleave/rez range.\n- **A few carries are dying a lot** — Ashton (DH, 15 deaths), VincentCross (13), Pentheus (12), Eliare (12 on a Druid support). Losing a healer 12 times is costly; worth a positioning/target-priority word with the backline DPS and that Druid.\n- **Turn on precise combat replay** — this run logged no positional data, so I can't tell you *where* those 296 deaths happened. With it on, next review can pinpoint out-of-position deaths and spread-at-the-bomb.\n\n**Double down on:** picking fights you can out-strip and out-cleave — the 1.63 K/D while outnumbered is the signature of good target calling here. **Change:** the down-to-death conversion — tighten pushes so more of those 575 downs get rezzed instead of finished.\n\nWant me to pull the same review for other recent nights (harasho, Jordan, etc.) to give Not Haro a baseline to compare against?","filedAt":"1:43 PM","tools":[{"name":"load_skill"},{"name":"axibridge_runs_list"},{"name":"axibridge_run_summary","display":{"kind":"table","data":{"title":"Not Haro — 32W/13L over 45 fights","columns":[{"key":"accou